      • buildModesRadioButton

        public void buildModesRadioButton(java.lang.String editRadiotext,
                         java.lang.String readRadioText)

        Build a radio buttons for the select mode action.

        The select mode action can be Edit or Reader, see TViewMode. If the parameters was null this will use the text set up in @TPresenter{decorator= @TDecorator{editModeTitle='', readerModeTitle='' }} but if the given TModelView was not annotated with TPresenter or with a custom view annotation which contains a TPresenter a default string (TAnnotationDefaultValue.TVIEW_editModeTitle and TAnnotationDefaultValue.TVIEW_readerModeTitle) will be used.

        This will initialize with "t-title-label" id.

      • buildEditButton

        public void buildEditButton(java.lang.String text)

        Build a button for the edit action.

        If the parameter was null this will use the text set up in @TPresenter{decorator= @TDecorator{editButtonText=''}} but if the given TModelView was not annotated with TPresenter or with a custom view annotation which contains a TPresenter a default string (TAnnotationDefaultValue.TVIEW_editButtonText) will be used.

        This will initialize with "t-button" id.
